f=Engineering/raj/custom/api-standards/SKILL.md · in=api-standards raj's contract discipline: API backend exposes consistent authentication authorization, explicit versioning, uniform error shapes, sane pagination, contract tests pin shape consumers don't break. protocol (REST, GraphQL, gRPC) comes stack-profile; discipline regardless. · p=Inconsistent APIs integrations break security holes open: one endpoint returns 200-with-error-body, another 500s; one checks authorization, next forgot; breaking change ships version bump client shatters. written standard makes API predictable predictable APIs testable, secure, safe evolve. · wu=Triggers: "design endpoint," "API design," "how errors look," "version API," "is breaking change," "contract test," any new changed backend surface. · st:/ Protocol=`An API surface to design/change \· -> AUTH: authentication on every non-public route; AUTHORIZATION per-object (not just per-route) \· -> VERSIONING: explicit; a breaking change bumps the version, never mutates a live contract \· -> ERROR SHAPE: one consistent error envelope (code, message, detail) — never 200-with-error \· -> PAGINATION / limits: bounded responses; no unbounded list endpoints (DoS + cost)` · in=**Auth route; authorization per-object.** Authentication (who) non-public endpoint, authorization (may they act object) checked per-resource IDOR hole aegis's review hunts. endpoint authenticates authorizes route level finding. **Version explicitly; breaking changes bump.** change removes field, changes type, alters semantics breaking bumps version never mutate live contract under existing clients. Additive changes (new optional field) safe within version. **One error shape, always.** single error envelope (stable machine-readable `code`, human `message`, optional `detail`) correct status codes never HTTP 200 wrapping error, never leaking stack traces internal structure (aegis's info-leak concern). Consumers handle errors uniformly all. **Bound response.** List endpoints paginate; endpoint returns unbounded data (it's cost DoS surface cypher's L10). Limits explicit enforced server-side. **Contract tests pin shape.** endpoint tests asserting request/response contract, breaking change fails (quinn's gate) rather client production. API-layer answer "agents say done" contract test proves shape real, claimed. **The shape reflects data model.** API resources map dana's schema; contract contradicts model integration bug. Deep N+1-prone data access follows data-access-discipline, raw queries handler. · of=`## API: [endpoint/surface] — [protocol per stack-profile] \· Auth: [authn ✓ \· authz per-object ✓] \· Version: [v \· breaking? bump] \· Error shape: [consistent envelope ✓ \· correct status] \· Pagination: [bounded ✓] \· Contract tests: [present, pin shape ✓] \· Security review: [n/a / →aegis] \· Data model fit: [reflects dana model ✓ / mismatch]` · pr=**Auth everywhere; authorization per-object** route-level-only check IDOR hole., **Version explicitly; breaking changes bump** never mutate live contract., **One error shape, correct status, leakage** uniform handling, 200-wrapped errors., **Bound response** unbounded lists cost DoS surfaces., **Contract tests pin shape** breaking changes fail CI, production clients., **The API reflects data model** contradictions integration bugs. · f=stack-profile protocol design REST-conventionally, flag missing standard dev; discipline holds regardless protocol., Breaking change genuinely unavoidable within version version bump deprecation window consumer notice, never silent break., Legacy inconsistent endpoints new endpoints follow standard; legacy ones get tracked debt entry, rewrite-everything mandate. · b:with Other Skills=**service-patterns** (sibling): service behind API behaves (idempotency, resilience); contract edge., **data-access-discipline** (sibling): handlers reach dana's stores without N+1 Rail-3 violations., **aegis/secure-code-review**: auth/input surfaces route security pass; S-tier quinn's gate., **dana**: data model API shape reflects; mismatches joint fixes., **mia**: frontend consumes contracts; contract tests protect boundary., **quinn**: contract tests gate evidence; unbounded/unversioned endpoints gate findings.